</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1437,151,1581]" box="[199,541,1412,1437]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">• Sponge large, cup-shaped.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="66" pageNumber="67" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1437,151,1581]" box="[199,819,1447,1473]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">• Texture firm, heavy crust of very fine sand present.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1437,151,1581]" box="[199,837,1484,1509]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">• Primary fibres thick and cored with foreign material.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1437,151,1581]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">• A dense mass of fine collagenous filaments, each enlargened terminally at both ends, occurs in the mesohyl.</paragraph>
